# Basic Filter Pushdown

## Description

Pushes a selection predicate below a projection when the predicate
references only columns retained by the projection.

## Relational Algebra

```algebra
σ[p](π[A](R)) -> π[A](σ[p](R))
  where attrs(p) ⊆ A
```

## Implementation

```rust
use egg::{rewrite as rw, *};

rw!("filter-pushdown-basic";
    "(filter ?pred (project ?cols ?rel))" =>
    "(project ?cols (filter ?pred ?rel))"
    if pred_attrs_subset_of(?pred, ?cols)
),
```

## Test Cases

### Positive Case 1: Simple pushdown

```sql
-- Input
SELECT name FROM employees WHERE age > 30;

-- Expected: filter pushed below projection
-- Plan: Project[name](Filter[age > 30](Scan(employees)))
```
